1 participating in or assisting an investigation, proceeding, or hearing under this
2 Chapter.
3 (14) Serious health condition. – An illness, injury, impairment, pregnancy,
4 recovery from childbirth, or physical or mental condition that involves
5 inpatient care in a hospital, hospice, or residential medical care facility, or
6 continuing treatment by a health care provider.
7 (15) State average weekly wage. – The average weekly insured wage as defined in
